Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.99,0:00:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to participate as guest in a travel program\Nfor Nichiuri TV, we came all the way to Hiroshima.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.64,0:00:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But strange incidents befell the TV staff members...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.73,0:00:18.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After we befriended the shopgirl Ayase Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from a\Nlong-established red leaf bun shop known as Misenya...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.82,0:00:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We learned that these incidents were in accordance\Nwith Misen's legendary seven wonders.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.12,0:00:28.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, the identity of the mystery man\Nthat'd been harassing the TV staff members...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.04,0:00:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was determined to likely be the older\Nbrother of Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.92,0:00:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two years earlier, an incident involving Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nparents had them fall to their death at Misen...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.21,0:00:42.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does it have something to do with the TV staff members?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.80,0:00:46.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, the director Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was attacked...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.68,0:00:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the Misenya shop was set on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.85,0:00:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was everything the work of Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.60,0:00:53.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or was it...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.85,0:01:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we continue lamenting the passing seasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.68,0:01:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be unable to confront the mysteries of cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.83,0:01:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The seven mysteries will be revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.47,0:01:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll learn the surprising culprit at the end of our trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.63,0:01:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.30,0:01:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.26,0:01:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.24,0:03:03.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\be5\fad(210,0)}Miyamoto Kenichi (55)\N{\fscy90\fscx75}Hiroshima Police First Division Inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.59,0:03:03.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm Miyamoto from the Hiroshima Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.40,0:03:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, may I ask how Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.15,0:03:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.45,0:03:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's unconscious and in critical condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.77,0:03:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.29,0:03:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.48,0:03:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit must be that bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.31,0:03:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so, detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.31,0:03:19.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we can't conclude that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.87,0:03:21.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.96,0:03:23.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard a lot about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.64,0:03:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.78,0:03:25.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bu culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.21,0:03:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mean Ayase Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from this Misenya shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.88,0:03:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pardon me, but you're Ayase{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s little sister, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.97,0:03:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you seen this before?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.85,0:03:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.23,0:03:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother's!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.35,0:03:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems this was dropped at the scene\Nwhere Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.31,0:03:43.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.52,0:03:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.69,0:03:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, the cause of fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.03,0:03:53.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't fully establish that yet, but the point of\Norigin was at the boundary of the adjacent store.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.62,0:03:56.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There weren't any inflammable materials\Nthere, suggesting this was probably arson.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.16,0:03:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.38,0:04:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around the time the fire broke out, people in the vicinity\Nwitnessed a man resembling your brother around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.38,0:04:12.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, it really was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.01,0:04:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her elder brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.73,0:04:17.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ayase Yayoi (22)\N"Misenya" Owner's Daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:16.52,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He assaulted Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and then torched his own home...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.60,0:04:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.60,0:04:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.89,0:04:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother wouldn't do something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.52,0:04:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.05,0:04:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.48,0:04:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if we assume Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What reason could he have to burn his own home?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.86,0:04:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.86,0:04:37.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of fire, isn't this another imitation of\None of the seven wonders â€”\hthe Eternal Fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.75,0:04:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.75,0:04:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The seven wonders, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.62,0:04:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.79,0:04:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I still think it's just coincidence, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.88,0:04:51.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.51,0:04:54.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, regarding your parents' deaths...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.26,0:05:00.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your brother suspects that the TV staff members, who happened to\Nbe around at the time of the accident, had something to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.02,0:05:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as such, he imitated the seven wonders and caused all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.10,0:05:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was only a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.44,0:05:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.65,0:05:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I confirmed with Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} earlier, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.65,0:05:15.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her parents' accident happened the day after we left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.32,0:05:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, her parents' accident\Nhad nothing to do with Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.41,0:05:23.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} mistook the whole\Nthing without knowing this fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.00,0:05:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, regarding Ayase Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s whereabouts...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.67,0:05:31.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will be the first priority for our police's investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:34.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother, where could you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.22,0:05:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although he's currently in hiding...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.47,0:05:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't say for sure that Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.60,0:05:43.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leading us to believe so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.56,0:05:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real culprit might be among those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.31,0:05:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, at the time Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was attacked...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.40,0:05:56.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hamada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Shimokura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and Yatsukawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were\Nwith us during the tour of the ordination platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.20,0:05:58.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyake{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was with Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.70,0:06:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called us from the\Nhotel in Hiroshima during the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.16,0:06:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It takes ten minutes to arrive at Miyajimaguchi by ferry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.63,0:06:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It then takes a further 25 minutes to arrive at\Nthe hotel in Hiroshima City by bullet train.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.84,0:06:14.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't make it in time even if he were to\Nattack Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and hurry back to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.76,0:06:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, it looks like the one without\Nan alibi would solely be Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.60,0:06:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.26,0:06:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\b0} there\NKaji... ita...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.60,0:06:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.15,0:06:28.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Misenya shop is on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.61,0:06:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By "kaji", he meant "fire"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.23,0:06:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like he thought "kaji" meant something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.90,0:06:41.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, it was impossible for Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to\Nhave known about the fire at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.49,0:06:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the "kaji" blurted out by Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.46,0:06:46.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:48.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.75,0:06:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will this photo be of assistance?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.09,0:06:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.63,0:06:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I happened to have one more copy on hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.88,0:07:00.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the ones I put up on display all got burnt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.31,0:07:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the target of the fire wasn't meant to be Misenya?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.86,0:07:11.06,Signs,,0,0,0,,Atomic Bomb Dome
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.33,0:07:14.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The next day, we returned to the city of Hiroshima...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.53,0:07:14.07,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hiroshima Peace Memorial Park
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:17.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And met up with Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who was resting in the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.53,0:07:17.04,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hiroshima Peace Memorial Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.40,0:07:21.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I deeply apologize for the inconvenience I caused yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.62,0:07:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, good as new.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.91,0:07:30.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About your stomachache, do you have\Nany idea who might've done this to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.55,0:07:32.70,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You mean the Seven Wonders imitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.59,0:07:34.55,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kitamura Yuuichi (32)\NNichiuri TV Assistant Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.71,0:07:34.55,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I just heard about it and was appalled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.42,0:07:38.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as I could recall, there was that lunch I had during filming...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.18,0:07:45.23,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kamisu Mikihiko (52)\NNichiuri TV Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.33,0:07:42.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Could it be that someone tampered with his lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:46.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What concerns me more is what we should do from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.32,0:07:52.36,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yatsukawa Kouiji (27)\NAssistant Director
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.83,0:07:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an}Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.18,0:07:50.92,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I know that Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is in a bad state right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.95,0:07:53.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And I understand that I shouldn't be saying this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.15,0:07:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, just spit it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.11,0:07:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think this is a once-in-a-lifetime chance for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.45,0:08:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Gourmet Tour Detective Solves the Caseâ€”On the Spot!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.28,0:08:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're guaranteed to get high ratings!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.25,0:08:08.21,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hamada Yukinari (40)\NCameraman
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.39,0:08:06.16,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I completely agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:08.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'd feel unsettled if we did nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.61,0:08:09.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.26,0:08:11.84,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Miyake Fumie (28)\NMakeup Artist
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.26,0:08:11.84,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shimokura Kazuya (25)\NSoundman
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.98,0:08:11.84,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That'd be a disgrace to Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.21,0:08:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please allow me to also regain my reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.17,0:08:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I beg of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.92,0:08:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.22,0:08:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll negotiate with the higher-ups myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.05,0:08:24.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yatsukawa, take on Koshiji's role for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.47,0:08:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.60,0:08:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you can see, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.72,0:08:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a slight change of plan in our\Nprogram, but can you still help us out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.48,0:08:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's decided, please count on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.73,0:08:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.55,0:08:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.86,0:08:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.11,0:08:42.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you, Hamada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.41,0:08:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.70,0:08:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.33,0:08:56.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} truly believed that the TV staff who visited Miyajima\Ntwo years ago had something to do with his parents' deaths...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.34,0:09:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's logical to assume that he imitated the seven wonders of Misen\Nwhere they died, and launched his attack on the staff members.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.89,0:09:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the ones who came to Miyajima two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.85,0:09:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were only Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and Miyake{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.22,0:09:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Yatsukawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't even there...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.06,0:09:16.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be strange for the culprit to imitate the\NEbb-and-Flow Rock wonder and put salt in his canned coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.81,0:09:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That really was strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.65,0:09:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well that's... because he's part of the staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.57,0:09:25.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a saying that goes, "He who\Nhates Peter harms his dog," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.41,0:09:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, exactly what you said!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.37,0:09:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying the next target could be me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.29,0:09:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's also possible that I'm the target.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.58,0:09:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless of who the culprit is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.50,0:09:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are likely to imitate the remaining\Nwonder of the "Dragon Fire Cedar"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.59,0:09:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And make their next heinous move, no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.15,0:09:50.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We then decided to meet up with\NShinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s friend in Hiroshima City.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:50.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shukkeien\N\N\N\N\NMiniature Scenery Garden
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.37,0:09:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.56,0:09:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} for over half a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.20,0:09:59.20,Signs,,0,0,0,,Rainbow Arch Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.71,0:09:58.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,After his parents died, Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} went off the deep end.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.00,0:10:04.78,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Unable to leave him alone, Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} quit her collage\Nprogram in Osaka and came back to Miyajima.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.15,0:10:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that person really the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.45,0:10:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The high-rise wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.33,0:10:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.05,0:10:21.09,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hiroshima Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.70,0:10:25.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.13,0:10:29.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know too well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.22,0:10:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.22,0:10:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a question about two years ago, can you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.06,0:10:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.28,0:10:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.53,0:10:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that really is how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.24,0:10:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.62,0:10:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} isn't here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.08,0:10:53.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.08,0:10:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where could he be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.42,0:10:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.18,0:11:15.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.44,0:11:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.82,0:11:24.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.24,0:11:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dragon pattern...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:31.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last of the seven wonders...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.45,0:11:33.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Dragon Fire Cedar's imitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.29,0:11:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cellphone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.33,0:11:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was he attacked from behind while he was on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, did you see the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.55,0:11:47.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.88,0:11:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I arrived here, Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was already on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.30,0:11:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, why were you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.51,0:11:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone called me, claiming to be calling on behalf of my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.85,0:12:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying that my brother wanted to talk to me about the truth he\Njust learned, and that he wanted to meet at Hiroshima Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.82,0:12:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A proxy, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.44,0:12:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that really so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.57,0:12:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you suspecting Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.70,0:12:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the brother's motive is to avenge his parents' deaths...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.28,0:12:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can assume that the sister shares the same motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.62,0:12:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.54,0:12:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'm next!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.50,0:12:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't even come here to film\Ntwo years ago and was still attacked regardless...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.30,0:12:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this is a case of an indifference assault,\Nthe rest of us might be attacked again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.72,0:12:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying it won't be just salt for me the next time!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.80,0:12:37.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it's an indifference attack, indifference!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.56,0:12:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, what a son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.82,0:12:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not about to let the culprit run amok anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.07,0:12:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's my turn to retaliate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.37,0:12:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.74,0:12:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} are...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.99,0:12:59.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dead!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.41,0:13:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.71,0:13:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just received word from the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.21,0:13:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My condolences.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.29,0:13:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.04,0:13:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the culprit really was this Ayase Shinroku guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we just finished paperwork seeking his arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.22,0:13:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.97,0:13:17.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.79,0:13:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's already under our protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.71,0:13:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was exactly as Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} deduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.29,0:13:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.21,0:13:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.72,0:13:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.97,0:13:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.27,0:14:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:05.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I have no idea what's going on either...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.49,0:14:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is the famous "Sleeping Kogorou" pose?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.24,0:14:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the culprit behind all these incidents was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.12,0:14:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By leading us to think Ayase Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} imitated Misen's\Nseven wonders in order to avenge his parents' deaths...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.96,0:14:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You managed to carry out your crime scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.84,0:14:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your target was the director, Koshiji Naoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.13,0:14:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The plan was to murder him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.72,0:14:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.10,0:14:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.18,0:14:44.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.89,0:14:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, why did he want to make Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} into his scapegoat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.52,0:14:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because, regarding the death\Nfall of his parents two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.53,0:14:56.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you, Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.95,0:14:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:15:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the autumn of two years ago,\Nafter the filming session ended...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.57,0:15:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You remained at Miyajima alone due\Nto mountain-hiking being your hobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.66,0:15:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard it from Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.50,0:15:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Miyake{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.13,0:15:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While climbing Misen, you entered the forbidden entry area...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.84,0:15:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And were reprimanded by Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what happened during that time, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their parents fell to their deaths as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.14,0:15:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} searched the vicinity and picked up\Nsomething resembling a piece of an accessory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.15,0:15:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was actually the zipper decoration\Non the jacket you were wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.36,0:15:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the exact same as the thing on the bag you're carrying right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.03,0:15:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.62,0:15:44.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.66,0:15:46.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.75,0:15:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The zipper on Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s jacket!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.79,0:15:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.88,0:15:53.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.79,0:15:59.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two years ago, Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} happened to borrow that jacket from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.38,0:16:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recall that he said, "Lend me that\Njacket, I feel like I'm catching a cold."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.51,0:16:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That zipper decoration was discovered\Nby Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} at the accident site.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.48,0:16:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you dropped that, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell us what happened then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.02,0:16:15.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.77,0:16:18.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We argued a little bit, and then suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.86,0:16:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know they'd end up like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.16,0:16:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll have the police thoroughly question\Nyou about the details of that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.29,0:16:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was two weeks ago that Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} realized\Nthe origin of the object he had picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.21,0:16:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quite possibly after looking at the photo from two years\Nago that was put on display by the souvenir shop owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.59,0:16:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, is that why Shiriroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} thought Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nhad something to do with his parents' accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.01,0:16:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.89,0:16:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a result, Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to Tokyo to verify his suspicions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.39,0:16:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:16:57.03,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ayase Shinroku (27)\NYayoi's Older Brother
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.64,0:16:55.61,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.62,0:16:56.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's exactly as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.61,0:17:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After arriving in Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.49,0:17:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I started to investigate that director named Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.07,0:17:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soon afterwards, this guy said he'd let me\Nmeet Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and wouldn't let me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.33,0:17:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who approached you was Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.75,0:17:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.79,0:17:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he called Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to Hiroshima\Nwhile the filming was taking place...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.21,0:17:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And confined him in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.30,0:17:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who imitated the seven\Nwonders and attacked Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.26,0:17:26.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And burned the photos that could become evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.55,0:17:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was actually Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} disguised as Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.09,0:17:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.43,0:17:35.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had an alibi, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.73,0:17:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called this hotel and received\Nconfirmation that he was sleeping...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.07,0:17:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And during the fire, Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called back too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.61,0:17:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}" the hotel staff member\Nsaw when she stopped by and checked...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.58,0:17:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was actually Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who was given sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.71,0:17:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By shaving off his mustache and changing his hairstyle...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.29,0:18:00.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could make sure that she wouldn't be able to\Ntell them apart when the police question her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.63,0:18:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nsuspected it was Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.47,0:18:07.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The high-rise wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.85,0:18:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.77,0:18:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that high-rise that can be seen outside the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.77,0:18:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't in the video call last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.19,0:18:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've found out what this was about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.69,0:18:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.44,0:18:28.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another hotel branch of ours\Nnear the Miyajimaguchi ferry terminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.66,0:18:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The interior was almost the same as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.37,0:18:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the hotel itself was also a double.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.21,0:18:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he crossed the sea by ferry, he immediately\Nchecked in to that particular nearby hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.42,0:18:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And promptly called Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to establish his alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.17,0:18:49.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, there is a difference between the two hotel rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.97,0:18:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the color of the curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.85,0:18:55.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although this one is sky blue, the one at\NMiyajimaguchi was peppermint green.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.48,0:18:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he couldn't close the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.48,0:19:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because of the contrasting night sceneries...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.07,0:19:04.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} discovered the trick that had been used.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.65,0:19:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.65,0:19:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, is this the Red Leaf Hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.70,0:19:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he smashed the cellphone was to prevent people\Nfrom noticing Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had made a call to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.38,0:19:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then called Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out, in the hope that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.42,0:19:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could frame her with the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.34,0:19:27.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.18,0:19:33.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like there had been a rumor about\Nsomeone running an illegal casino.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.97,0:19:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, wasn't that about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.89,0:19:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s final message...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.52,0:19:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fire there\NKaji... ita...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.90,0:19:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He actually meant "casino" and "Kitamura".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.70,0:19:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had already noticed your true color.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.33,0:19:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My guess is that he asked you to turn\Nyourself over to the police, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.20,0:20:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead, you tried to put it in Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nhead that Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the suspicious one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.33,0:20:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why during filming, the atmosphere between\NKamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was unsettling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.84,0:20:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that after murdering Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you also planned\Nto frame him with the crime of running the illegal casino?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:16.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that casino...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.81,0:20:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was only trying to have some fun at first, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.02,0:20:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suddenly everything was blown out of\Ncontrol, and I had no way to quit anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.73,0:20:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just couldn't help it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.82,0:20:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't help it, so you assaulted\NKoshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.78,0:20:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And decided to frame Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with the\Ncrimes you committed, ruining his life?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.24,0:20:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think you can get away...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.29,0:20:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With such an egocentric excuse!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.68,0:20:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I almost forgot to say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.76,0:20:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} nor Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.06,0:21:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just received a report from the hospital that both of\Nthem have stabilized and are responding to treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.82,0:21:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all part of my instruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.40,0:21:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologize for lying to you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.91,0:21:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the reason I did that was to allow the real culprit to\Nlower his guard and proceed to frame Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.58,0:22:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, Koshiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Kamisuwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nsteadily recovered from their injuries...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.75,0:22:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Shinroku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} reunited with Yayoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nrejoicing in each other's well-being.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.43,0:23:06.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.73,0:23:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Hiroshima-style okonomiyaki is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.77,0:23:13.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The beer is awesome too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.94,0:23:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.07,0:23:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I wonder what will become of the program?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.78,0:23:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, they'd better have it broadcast!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.08,0:23:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is my first time I'd be able to see\Nmyself making a great deduction!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.25,0:23:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, since you're always asleep, you Sleeping Kogorou.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.46,0:23:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder where Sonoko is now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.84,0:23:38.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speak of the devil...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.34,0:23:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko, where on earth are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.72,0:23:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.76,0:23:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.56,0:23:46.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This island is so soothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.60,0:23:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Island!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.77,0:23:50.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really awesome in Miyakojima!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.27,0:23:54.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She mistook the name and went to Miyakojima instead...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.19,0:23:57.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.45,0:24:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what every kid likes...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.26,0:24:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Masked Yaiba" show is also produced here!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.24,0:24:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just watched it last week...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.07,0:24:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The back of the body is soaking wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.18,0:24:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Given that the rain already stopped, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.64,0:24:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a murder case disguised as suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.72,0:24:32.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
